			                        Too many problems
			                        Pickle
			                        2017/01/31
			                        
				                        
					                         
				                        
			                        
			                    
			                    
			                        I purchased Windows 10 complete with a new top of the range desk top computer for my business around 10 months ago, I run 3 on-line businesses.
Some users seem to love it and don’t appear to have any problems, or so they say!  However, in my case it’s been a nightmare…in the past, from Win 95 through to XP and onwards to Windows 7, I have never required support and what few problems I had with drivers etc, I sorted myself.
Multiple attempts to sort the numerous issues with Contana plus other issues, ad-nauseam, have resulted in sleepless nights and total frustration together with the added worry of trying to run a business on an unreliable and capricious platform.
I feel desperately sorry for the Microsoft Technicians that have worked on my machine, they do their very best, given the time constraints and the resources at their disposal.
When it works, it’s great…fast, informative and up to date with the latest quirks of the IT industry…I like it, I want to like it, I don’t want to give up, but until Microsoft get it sorted once and for all, I’d avoid it if you can and continue with the best and most stable platforms ever produced and they are:  XP & 7…I pay my way, I don’t want anything for free, I’d rather pay for software and have it work, I can’t afford the time to do otherwise.
